Add cache_to field (Optional[str])\n63: - [ ] Add dockerfile_content field (Optional[str])\n64: - [ ] Add validators for all fields\n65: - [ ] Add comprehensive docstrings\n66: \n67: **Verification**: Run `python -c \"from agentcube.models.build_models import BuildMetadata; m = BuildMetadata(build_context='.'); print(m)\" and verify it works\n68: \n69: ---\n70: \n71: ### Task 6: Create PublishMetadata model for publish command\n72: - [ ] Define PublishMetadata class extending BaseModel in models/publish_models.py\n73: - [ ] Add image_name field (str)\n74: - [ ] Add image_tag field (str, default=\"latest\")\n75: - [ ] Add registry_url field (Optional[str])\n76: - [ ] Add registry_username field (Optional[str])\n77: - [ ] Add registry_password field (Optional[str])\n78: - [ ] Add build_metadata field (Optional[BuildMetadata])\n79: - [ ] Add validators for image_name (valid Docker image name format)\n80: - [ ] Add validators for image_tag (valid Docker tag format)\n81: - [ ] Add comprehensive docstrings\n82: \n83: **Verification**: Run `python -c \"from agentcube.models.publish_models import PublishMetadata; m = PublishMetadata(image_name='test'); print(m)\" and verify it works\n84: \n85: ---\n86: \n87: ### Task 7: Create InvokeMetadata model for invoke command\n88: - [ ] Define InvokeMetadata class extending BaseModel in models/invoke_models.py\n89: - [ ] Add agent_endpoint field (str)\n90: - [ ] Add session_id field (Optional[str])\n91: - [ ] Add timeout_seconds field (int, default=30)\n92: - [ ] Add retry_count field (int, default=0)\n93: - [ ] Add retry_delay_seconds field (int, default=1)\n94: - [ ] Add input_data field (Optional[Dict[str, Any]])\n95: - [ ] Add stream_output field (bool, default=False)\n96: - [ ] Add validators for timeout_seconds (must be positive)\n97: - [ ] Add validators for retry_count (must be non-negative)\n98: - [ ] Add comprehensive docstrings\n99: \n100: **Verification**: Run `python -c \"from agentcube.models.invoke_models import InvokeMetadata; m = InvokeMetadata(agent_endpoint='http://localhost:8080'); print(m)\" and verify it works\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ### Task 8: Create StatusMetadata model for status command\n105: - [ ] Define StatusMetadata class extending BaseModel in models/status_models.py\n106: - [ ] Add agent_id field (Optional[str])\n107: - [ ] Add session_id field (Optional[str])\n108: - [ ] Add workspace_path field (Optional[str])\n109: - [ ] Add verbose field (bool, default=False)\n110: - [ ] Add include_logs field (bool, default=False)\n111: - [ ] Add include_metrics field (bool, default=False)\n112: - [ ] Add validators for at least one identifier field must be present\n113: - [ ] Add comprehensive docstrings\n114: \n115: **Verification**: Run `python -c \"from agentcube.models.status_models import StatusMetadata; m = StatusMetadata(); print(m)\" and verify it works\n116: \n117: ---\n118: \n119: ### Task 9: Update models/__init__.py to export all model classes\n120: - [ ] Add import for AgentMetadata from .metadata\n121: - [ ] Add import for BuildMetadata from .build_models\n122: - [ ] Add import for PublishMetadata from .publish_models\n123: - [ ] Add import for InvokeMetadata from .invoke_models\n124: - [ ] Add import for StatusMetadata from .status_models\n125: - [ ] Keep existing MetadataOptions export\n126: - [ ] Update module docstring to document all exported classes\n127: - [ ] Verify all exports are accessible\n128: \n129: **Verification**: Run `python -c \"from agentcube.models import AgentMetadata, BuildMetadata, PublishMetadata, InvokeMetadata, StatusMetadata; print('All models imported')\" and verify it works\n130: \n131: ---\n132: \n133: ### Task 10: Enhance MetadataService.load_metadata with better error handling\n134: - [ ] Add try-except block around YAML loading\n135: - [ ] Add specific handling for yaml.YAMLError\n136: - [ ] Add specific handling for pydantic.ValidationError\n137: - [ ] Improve error messages with file context\n138: - [ ] Add line number to error messages for YAML errors\n139: - [ ] Add field name to error messages for validation errors\n140: - [ ] Log detailed error information in verbose mode\n141: \n142: **Verification**: Create malformed YAML file and verify clear error message with context is displayed\n143: \n144: ---\n145: \n146: ### Task 11: Add MetadataService.validate_metadata method\n147: - [ ] Define validate_metadata method with metadata parameter\n148: - [ ] Run all Pydantic validators on metadata\n149: - [ ] Add custom validation for workspace-specific fields\n150: - [ ] Check if required files exist based on metadata\n151: - [ ] Return validation result with list of errors and warnings\n152: - [ ] Add comprehensive docstring\n153: - [ ] Add logging for validation results\n154: \n155: **Verification**: Create test metadata with various validation issues and verify all errors are reported\n156: \n157: ---\n158: \n159: ### Task 12: Add MetadataService.merge_metadata method\n160: - [ ] Define merge_metadata method with base_metadata and updates parameters\n161: - [ ] Deep merge nested dictionaries (image, auth, k8s_deployment)\n162: - [ ] Override scalar fields from updates\n163: - [ ] Preserve None values as intended deletions\n164: - [ ] Run validation on merged result\n165: - [ ] Return merged AgentMetadata instance\n166: - [ ] Add comprehensive docstring\n167: \n168: **Verification**: Create base metadata, merge updates, and verify correct merging behavior\n169: \n170: ---\n171: \n172: ### Task 13: Add MetadataService.infer_metadata method\n173: - [ ] Define infer_metadata method with workspace_path parameter\n174: - [ ] Detect language based on file extensions (.py, .java, pom.xml)\n175: - [ ] Infer entrypoint from common patterns (main.py, app.py, server.py)\n176: - [ ] Infer port from common patterns (8080 default, check for PORT env var)\n177: - [ ] Infer build_mode based on existing Dockerfile\n178: - [ ] Infer requirements_file based on language\n179: - [ ] Return inferred AgentMetadata with all defaults\n180: - [ ] Add comprehensive docstring\n181: \n182: **Verification**: Create test workspaces with different structures and verify correct inference\n183: \n184: ---\n185: \n186: ### Task 14: Add MetadataService.export_metadata method\n187: - [ ] Define export_metadata method with metadata and format parameters\n188: - [ ] Support YAML export format (default)\n189: - [ ] Support JSON export format\n190: - [ ] Support environment variable export format\n191: - [ ] Handle format-specific serialization\n192: - [ ] Write to specified output file or stdout\n193: - [ ] Add comprehensive docstring\n194: \n195: **Verification**: Export metadata in different formats and verify correct output\n196: \n197: ---\n198: \n199: ### Task 15: Add MetadataService.get_metadata_diff method\n200: - [ ] Define get_metadata_diff method with old_metadata and new_metadata parameters\n201: - [ ] Compare all fields between two AgentMetadata instances\n202: - * ] Identify added fields\n203: - [ ] Identify removed fields\n204: - [ ] Identify changed fields with old and new values\n205: - [ ] Return structured diff dictionary\n206: - [ ] Add comprehensive docstring\n207: - [ ] Add logging for diff results\n208: \n209: **Verification**: Create two metadata instances and verify correct diff is computed\n210: \n211: ---\n212: \n213: ### Task 16: Consolidate duplicate MetadataOptions class\n214: - [ ] Remove MetadataOptions from models/__init__.py\n215: - [ ] Keep MetadataOptions in models/pack_models.py only\n216: - [ ] Update all imports to use MetadataOptions from pack_models\n217: - [ ] Verify no duplicate definitions exist\n218: - [ ] Verify all functionality still works\n219: \n220: **Verification**: Run `python -c \"from agentcube.models.pack_models import MetadataOptions; opts = MetadataOptions(); print(opts)\" and verify it works\n221: \n222: ---\n223: \n224: ### Task 17: Add comprehensive type hints to MetadataService\n225: - [ ] Add type hints to all method pa