{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875588585,"sessionID":"ses_28591995dffecxgKBgGgR4Fdd1","part":{"id":"prt_d7a6f0197001EjRuCF2ArwyYVu","messageID":"msg_d7a6edee6001WIgimxw3DjxLX3","sessionID":"ses_28591995dffecxgKBgGgR4Fdd1","type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"toolu_tool-2351995f4e82476cbdb7f021b97a9089","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"include":"*.md","path":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z","pattern":"k8s|kubernetes|K8s|Kubernetes"},"output":"Found 1666 matches (showing first 100)\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-026/design.md:\n  Line 1: # AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider Design\n  Line 3: ## AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider\n  Line 8: **Purpose**: Implement Kubernetes provider for agent deployment, enabling both standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service resources and AgentCube Custom Resources (AgentRuntime) for agent lifecycle management.\n  Line 14: The Kubernetes provider enables the AgentCube CLI to deploy and manage agents on Kubernetes clusters using two deployment strategies:\n  Line 16: 1. **Standard K8s Provider**: Creates native Kubernetes `Deployment` and `NodePort Service` resources\n  Line 19: Both providers share common interfaces through the `KubernetesProvider` and `AgentCubeProvider` service classes, which are integrated into the CLI via `PublishRuntime` and `StatusRuntime` classes.\n  Line 43: │   ├── k8s_provider.py            # KubernetesProvider (standard K8s)\n  Line 61:          ├──> PublishRuntime ──┬──> KubernetesProvider ──> K8s API\n  Line 64:          │                     └──> AgentCubeProvider ──> K8s API\n  Line 67:          ├──> StatusRuntime ──┬──> KubernetesProvider ──> K8s API\n  Line 70:          │                    └──> AgentCubeProvider ──> K8s API\n  Line 73:          ├──> InvokeRuntime ──┬──> Direct HTTP (K8s Service)\n  Line 91: - `--provider k8s`: Uses `KubernetesProvider` for standard Deployment/Service\n  Line 122:     k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n  Line 172: ### Kubernetes Deployment Info\n  Line 191: ### KubernetesProvider Interface\n  Line 194: class KubernetesProvider:\n  Line 275:     def _publish_cr_to_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n  Line 277:     def _publish_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n  Line 301: class KubernetesError(ProviderError):\n  Line 302:     \"\"\"Kubernetes provider specific errors\"\"\"\n  Line 309: class DeploymentTimeoutError(KubernetesError):\n  Line 317: 2. **Kubernetes Connection Failures**: Raise `KubernetesError` with detailed message\n  Line 336: ├── test_k8s_provider.py          # KubernetesProvider tests\n  Line 343:     └── mock_k8s_responses.py\n  Line 348: 1. **KubernetesProvider Tests**:\n  Line 369:    - Full publish flow with mock Kubernetes API\n  Line 375: - Use `unittest.mock` for Kubernetes API calls\n  Line 383: - `k8s_provider.py`\n  Line 390: ### Kubernetes API Integration\n  Line 392: **Kubernetes Client Initialization**:\n  Line 394: from kubernetes import client, config\n  Line 396: def _get_k8s_client(kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None):\n  Line 404: **Kubernetes API Endpoints**:\n  Line 487: k8s = [\n  Line 488:     \"kubernetes>=28.0.0\",\n  Line 498:     \"kubernetes>=28.0.0\",\n  Line 508: - **Kubernetes Cluster**: Access via kubeconfig or in-cluster config\n  Line 518:    - Package installation: `pip install agentcube-cli[k8s]`\n  Line 519:    - Kubernetes cluster setup\n  Line 525:    - Publishing to Kubernetes: `kubectl-agentcube publish --provider k8s`\n  Line 528:    - **Standard K8s Provider**: Using Deployment/Service resources\n  Line 533:    - `kubectl-agentcube publish` --provider k8s --namespace default --replicas 3\n  Line 540:    - Kubernetes API interaction patterns\n  Line 544:    - `KubernetesProvider` class documentation\n  Line 562: ### Kubernetes Auth