client code for API group **`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` / `v1alpha1`**, module path **`github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`**. Source reference: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`.\n  Line 853: **Regeneration:** `make gen-client` → `hack/update-codegen.sh` (`k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1, `--with-watch`, output package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`).\n  Line 1247: - **THEN** `base_url` SHALL resolve from `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; token SHALL resolve from `auth_token` or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` via `read_token_from_file`, and if present set `Authorization: Bearer {token}`\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md:\n  Line 1: # Delta Specification: AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider\n  Line 11: Implement dual provider support in the AgentCube CLI for deploying AI agents to Kubernetes: a standard provider using native Deployment and Service resources, and an AgentCube provider using the AgentRuntime custom resource (CR) for enhanced lifecycle management.\n  Line 22: - `--provider` flag accepts `k8s` or `agentcube` values\n  Line 34: #### Scenario 1.2: Valid provider selection - k8s\n  Line 35: - **GIVEN** the user specifies `--provider k8s`\n  Line 37: - **THEN** the system SHALL route deployment operations to `KubernetesProvider`\n  Line 47: - **THEN** the system SHALL print an error message indicating valid options are `k8s` or `agentcube` and exit with code `1`\n  Line 51: ## REQ-002: Kubernetes provider — Deployment creation\n  Line 53: ### Requirement: Create Kubernetes Deployment resource\n  Line 55: System SHALL create a Kubernetes `Deployment` resource with configurable replicas, container port, and optional environment variables when using the `k8s` provider.\n  Line 69: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `k8s`, `replicas` is `1` (default), and no env_vars are provided\n  Line 70: - **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent` is called with `agent_name`, `image_url`, and `port`\n  Line 80: - **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent` is called\n  Line 85: - **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent` is called\n  Line 88: #### Scenario 2.4: Name sanitization for K8s compliance\n\n(Results truncated: showing 100 of 1666 matches (1566 hidden). Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":1666,"truncated":true},"title":"k8s|kubernetes|K8s|Kubernetes","time":{"start":1775875588546,"end":1775875588582}}}}
