{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875592531,"sessionID":"ses_28591995dffecxgKBgGgR4Fdd1","part":{"id":"prt_d7a6f1115001BktrMFpvGPzGiv","messageID":"msg_d7a6f023d0018kv5fhMrrmuNvv","sessionID":"ses_28591995dffecxgKBgGgR4Fdd1","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-f5eb18fbd88c41998826f97f024efd50","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-026/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-026/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider Design\n2: \n3: ## AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider\n4: \n5: **Module**: `cmd/cli`\n6: **Language**: Python\n7: **Size**: M\n8: **Purpose**: Implement Kubernetes provider for agent deployment, enabling both standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service resources and AgentCube Custom Resources (AgentRuntime) for agent lifecycle management.\n9: \n10: ## Architecture\n11: \n12: ### Overview\n13: \n14: The Kubernetes provider enables the AgentCube CLI to deploy and manage agents on Kubernetes clusters using two deployment strategies:\n15: \n16: 1. **Standard K8s Provider**: Creates native Kubernetes `Deployment` and `NodePort Service` resources\n17: 2. **AgentCube Provider**: Creates `AgentRuntime` Custom Resources (CRD) managed by the AgentCube operator\n18: \n19: Both providers share common interfaces through the `KubernetesProvider` and `AgentCubeProvider` service classes, which are integrated into the CLI via `PublishRuntime` and `StatusRuntime` classes.\n20: \n21: ### Package Structure\n22: \n23: ```\n24: agentcube/\n25: ├── __init__.py                    # Package exports\n26: ├── cli/\n27: │   ├── __init__.py\n28: │   └── main.py                    # Typer CLI commands (pack, build, publish, invoke, status)\n29: ├── models/\n30: │   ├── __init__.py\n31: │   └── pack_models.py             # MetadataOptions dataclass\n32: ├── runtime/\n33: │   ├── __init__.py                # Runtime exports\n34: │   ├── pack_runtime.py            # PackRuntime class\n35: │   ├── build_runtime.py           # BuildRuntime class\n36: │   ├── publish_runtime.py         # PublishRuntime class\n37: │   ├── invoke_runtime.py          # InvokeRuntime class\n38: │   └── status_runtime.py          # StatusRuntime class\n39: ├── services/\n40: │   ├── __init__.py\n41: │   ├── metadata_service.py        # AgentMetadata model & persistence\n42: │   ├── docker_service.py          # Docker image operations\n43: │   ├── k8s_provider.py            # KubernetesProvider (standard K8s)\n44: │   └── agentcube_provider.py      # AgentCubeProvider (AgentRuntime CR)\n45: └── operations/\n46:     └── __init__.py                # Placeholder for future operations\n47: ```\n48: \n49: ### Component Interactions\n50: \n51: ```\n52: ┌─────────────────┐\n53: │  CLI (Typer)    │\n54: │  - pack         │\n55: │  - build        │\n56: │  - publish      │\n57: │  - invoke       │\n58: │  - status       │\n59: └────────┬────────┘\n60:          │\n61:          ├──> PublishRuntime ──┬──> KubernetesProvider ──> K8s API\n62:          │                     │    (Deployment + Service)\n63:          │                     │\n64:          │                     └──> AgentCubeProvider ──> K8s API\n65:          │                          (AgentRuntime CR)\n66:          │\n67:          ├──> StatusRuntime ──┬──> KubernetesProvider ──> K8s API\n68:          │                    │    (Deployment/Service status)\n69:          │                    │\n70:          │                    └──> AgentCubeProvider ──> K8s API\n71:          │                         (AgentRuntime CR status)\n72:          │\n73:          ├──> InvokeRuntime ──┬──> Direct HTTP (K8s Service)\n74:          │                    │\n75:          │                    └──> Router HTTP (AgentRuntime)\n76:          │\n77:          └──> MetadataService ──> agent_metadata.yaml\n78: \n79: ┌─────────────────┐\n80: │  DockerService  │\n81: │  - build_image  │\n82: │  - push_image   │\n83: └─────────────────┘\n84: ```\n85: \n86: ### Provider Selection\n87: \n88: Provider is selected via the `--provider` CLI option:\n89: \n90: - `--provider agentcube` (default): Uses `AgentCubeProvider` for AgentRuntime CR\n91: - `--provider k8s`: Uses `KubernetesProvider` for standard Deployment/Service\n92: \n93: ## Data Structures\n94: \n95: ### AgentMetadata (Pydantic BaseModel)\n96: \n97: ```python\n98: from pydantic import BaseModel, Field, validator\n99: \n100: class AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n101:     agent_name: str = Field(..., description=\"Unique name identifying the agent\")\n102:     description: Optional[str] = None\n103:     language: str = \"python\"\n104:     entrypoint: str = Field(..., description=\"Command to launch the agent\")\n105:     port: int = 8080\n106:     build_mode: str = \"local\"\n107:     region: Optional[str] = None\n108:     version: Optional[str] = None\n109:     image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n110:     auth: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n111:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = \"requirements.txt\"\n112:     registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n113:     registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n114:     registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n115:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = None\n116:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None\n117:     router_url: Optional[str] = None\n118:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None\n119:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None\n120:     agent_id: Optional[str] = None\n121:     session_id: Optional[str] = None\n122:     k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n123: \n124:     @validator('language')\n125:     def validate_language(cls, v):\n126:         if v.lower() not in ['python', 'java']:\n127:             raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported language: {v}\")\n128:         return v.lower()\n129: \n130:     @validator('build_mode')\n131:     def validate_build_mode(cls, v):\n132:         if v.lower() not in ['local', 'cloud']:\n133:             raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported build_mode: {v}\")\n134:         return v.lower()\n135: \n136:     @validator('port')\n137:     def validate_port(cls, v):\n138:         if not 1 <= v <= 65535:\n139:             raise ValueError(f\"Port must be between 1 and 65535, got {v}\")\n140:         return v\n141: ```\n142: \n143: ### MetadataOptions (Dataclass)\n144: \n145: ```python\n146: from dataclasses import dataclass\n147: from typing import Optional, Dict, Any\n148: \n149: @dataclass\n150: class MetadataOptions:\n151:     agent_name: Optional[str] = None\n152:     language: Optional[str] = 'python'\n153:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = None\n154:     port: Optional[int] = 8080\n155:     build_mode: Optional[str] = 'local'\n156:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = None\n157:     description: Optional[str] = None\n158:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n159:     router_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n160:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = \"\"\n161:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = 8080\n162:     registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n163:     registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n164:     registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n165:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = \"\"\n166: \n167:     @classmethod\n168:     def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\":\n169:         return cls(**{k: v for k, v in options.items() if k in cls.__dataclass_fields__})\n170: ```\n171: \n172: ### Kubernetes Deployment Info\n173: \n174: ```python\n175: {\n176:     \"type\": \"Deployment\",\n177:     \"deployment_name\": str,\n178:     \"service_name\": str,\n179:     \"namespace\": str,\n180:     \"replicas\": int,\n181:     \"container_port\": int,\n182:     \"node_port\": int,\n183:     \"service_url\": str,\n184:     \"status\": str,\n185:     \"last_updated\": str\n186: }\n187: ```\n188: \n189: ## API Contracts\n190: \n191: ### KubernetesProvider Interface\n192: \n193: ```python\n194: class KubernetesProvider:\n195:     def __init__(\n196:         self,\n197:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n198:         verbose: bool = False,\n199:         kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n200:     ) -> None: ...\n201: \n202:     def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None: ...\n203: \n204:     def deploy_agent(\n205:         self,\n206:         agent_name: str,\n207:         image_url: str,\n208:         port: int,\n209:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n210:         replicas: int = 1,\n211:         node_port: Optional[int] = None,\n212:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n213:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n214: \n215:     def _create_deployment(\n216:         self,\n217:         name: str,\n218:         image_url: str,\n219:         port: int,\n220:         entrypoint: Optional[str],\n221:         replicas: int,\n222:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n223:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n224: \n225:     def _create_service(self, name: str, port: int, node_port: Optional[int]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n226: \n227:     def wait_for_deployment_ready(self, name: str, timeout: int = 120) -> None: ...\n228: \n229:     def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n230: \n231:     def delete_agent(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n232: \n233:     def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str: ...\n234: ```\n235: \n236: ### AgentCubeProvider Interface\n237: \n238: ```python\n239: class AgentCubeProvider:\n240:     def __init__(\n241:         self,\n242:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n243:         verbose: bool = False,\n244:         kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n245:     ) -> None: ...\n246: \n247:     def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None: ...\n248: \n249:     def deploy_agent_runtime(\n250:         self,\n251:         agent_name: str,\n252:         image_url: str,\n253:         port: int,\n254:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n255:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n256:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n257:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n258:         readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None,\n259:         readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None,\n260:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n261: \n262:     def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str: ...\n263: \n264:     def get_agent_runtime(self, name: str, namespace: str) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]: ...\n265: ```\n266: \n267: ### PublishRuntime Interface\n268: \n269: ```python\n270: class PublishRuntime:\n271:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n272: \n273:     def publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n274: \n275:     def _publish_cr_to_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n276: \n277:     def _publish_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n278: \n279:     def _prepare_image_for_publishing(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n280: \n281:     def _prepare_local_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n282: \n283:     def _prepare_cloud_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n284: \n285:     def _update_publish_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, agent_info: Dict[str, Any]) -> None: ...\n286: ```\n287: \n288: ## Error Handling\n289: \n290: ### Exception Hierarchy\n291: \n292: ```python\n293: class AgentCubeError(Exception):\n294:     \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube\"\"\"\n295:     pass\n296: \n297: class ProviderError(AgentCubeError):\n298:     \"\"\"Base exception for provider operations\"\"\"\n299:     pass\n300: \n301: class KubernetesError(ProviderError):\n302:     \"\"\"Kubernetes provider specific errors\"\"\"\n303:     pass\n304: \n305: class AgentCubeProviderError(ProviderError):\n306:     \"\"\"AgentCube provider specific errors\"\"\"\n307:     pass\n308: \n309: class DeploymentTimeoutError(KubernetesError):\n310:     \"\"\"Raised when deployment fails to become ready within timeout\"\"\"\n311:     pass\n312: ```\n313: \n314: ### Error Handling Patterns\n315: \n316: 1. **Docker Unavailability**: Raise `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")`\n317: 2. **Kubernetes Connection Failures**: Raise `KubernetesError` with detailed message\n318: 3. **Missing Prerequisites**: Raise `ValueError` with clear instructions\n319: 4. **Deployment Timeout**: Raise `TimeoutError` after configured timeout\n320: 5. **CR Not Found**: Return `None` or appropriate status indicator\n321: 6. **Validation Failures**: Raise `ValueError` with field-specific details\n322: \n323: ### Error Recovery\n324: \n325: - **Namespace Creation**: Auto-create namespace if it doesn't exist\n326: - **Resource Updates**: Use `patch` instead of `create` to allow idempotent operations\n327: - **Session Cleanup**: Ensure sessions are deleted on context manager exit\n328: - **Rollback on Failure**: Revert version increment if build fails\n329: \n330: ## Testing Strategy\n331: \n332: ### Unit Tests\n333: \n334: ```python\n335: tests/\n336: ├── test_k8s_provider.py          # KubernetesProvider tests\n337: ├── test_agentcube_provider.py    # AgentCubeProvider tests\n338: ├── test_publish_runtime.py       # PublishRuntime tests\n339: ├── test_status_runtime.py        # StatusRuntime tests\n340: ├── test_metadata_service.py      # MetadataService tests\n341: └── fixtures/\n342:     ├── test_agent_metadata.yaml\n343:     └── mock_k8s_responses.py\n344: ```\n345: \n346: ### Test Scenarios\n347: \n348: 1. **KubernetesProvider Tests**:\n349:    - Namespace creation and validation\n350:    - Deployment creation with various configurations\n351:    - Service creation with NodePort assignment\n352:    - Status retrieval for different deployment states\n353:    - Resource deletion with proper cleanup\n354:    - Name sanitization (DNS-1123 compliance)\n355: \n356: 2. **AgentCubeProvider Tests**:\n357:    - AgentRuntime CR creation\n358:    - Environment variable injection (WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL, ROUTER_URL)\n359:    - Readiness probe configuration\n360:    - CR status retrieval\n361: \n362: 3. **PublishRuntime Tests**:\n363:    - Provider selection logic\n364:    - Image preparation (local vs cloud)\n365:    - Metadata updates after deployment\n366:    - Error handling for missing prerequisites\n367: \n368: 4. **Integration Tests**:\n369:    - Full publish flow with mock Kubernetes API\n370:    - Status check after successful deployment\n371:    - Error propagation through the stack\n372: \n373: ### Mocking Strategy\n374: \n375: - Use `unittest.mock` for Kubernetes API calls\n376: - Use `pytest-mock` for fixtures and side effects\n377: - Mock Docker SDK for build/push operations\n378: - Use `httpx.MockTransport` for HTTP client testing\n379: \n380: ### Test Coverage\n381: \n382: Target >80% coverage for:\n383: - `k8s_provider.py`\n384: - `agentcube_provider.py`\n385: - `publish_runtime.py`\n386: - `status_runtime.py`\n387: \n388: ## Integration Points\n389: \n390: ### Kubernetes API Integration\n391: \n392: **Kubernetes Client Initialization**:\n393: ```python\n394: from kubernetes import client, config\n395: \n396: def _get_k8s_client(kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None):\n397:     if kubeconfig:\n398:         config.load_kube_config(config_file=kubeconfig)\n399:     else:\n400:         config.load_incluster_config()\n401:     return client.AppsV1Api(), client.CoreV1Api(), client.CustomObjectsApi()\n402: ```\n403: \n404: **Kubernetes API Endpoints**:\n405: \n406: | Resource | Type | Endpoint |\n407: |----------|------|----------|\n408: | Deployment | `apps/v1` | `/apis/apps/v1/namespaces/{ns}/deployments/{name}` |\n409: | Service | `core/v1` | `/api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/services/{name}` |\n410: | Namespace | `core/v1` | `/api/v1/namespaces/{name}` |\n411: | AgentRuntime | Custom | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes/{name}` |\n412: \n413: ### Docker Service Integration\n414: \n415: ```python\n416: class DockerService:\n417:     def build_image(\n418:         self,\n419:         dockerfile_path: Path,\n420:         context_path: Path,\n421:         image_name: str,\n422:         tag: str = \"latest\",\n423:         build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n424:     ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n425: \n426:     def push_image(\n427:         self,\n428:         image_name: str,\n429:         registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n430:         username: Optional[str] = None,\n431:         password: Optional[str] = None,\n432:     ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n433: ```\n434: \n435: ### Metadata Service Integration\n436: \n437: ```python\n438: class MetadataService:\n439:     def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n440:     def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n441:     def update_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n442: ```\n443: \n444: ### CLI Integration\n445: \n446: ```python\n447: @app.command()\n448: def publish(\n449:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\"),\n450:     version: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--version\"),\n451:     image_url: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-url\"),\n452:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\"),\n453:     node_port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--node-port\"),\n454:     replicas: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--replicas\"),\n455:     namespace: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--namespace\"),\n456:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\"),\n457: ) -> None:\n458:     try:\n459:         runtime = PublishRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)\n460:         workspace_path = Path(workspace)\n461:         result = runtime.publish(workspace_path, **locals())\n462:         console.print(f\"[green]Agent published successfully![/green]\")\n463:         console.print(f\"Agent ID: {result['agent_id']}\")\n464:     except Exception as e:\n465:         _handle_error(e, \"publish\", verbose)\n466: ```\n467: \n468: ## Dependencies\n469: \n470: ### Required Dependencies (from pyproject.toml)\n471: \n472: ```toml\n473: [project]\n474: dependencies = [\n475:     \"typer[all]>=0.9.0\",\n476:     \"pydantic>=2.0.0\",\n477:     \"pyyaml>=6.0\",\n478:     \"httpx>=0.24.0\",\n479:     \"docker>=6.0.0\",\n480:     \"rich>=13.0.0\",\n481:     \"packaging>=23.0\",\n482:     \"importlib-resources>=6.0.0\",\n483:     \"semver>=3.0.0\",\n484: ]\n485: \n486: [project.optional-dependencies]\n487: k8s = [\n488:     \"kubernetes>=28.0.0\",\n489: ]\n490: \n491: dev = [\n492:     \"pytest>=7.4.0\",\n493:     \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\",\n494:     \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\",\n495:     \"ruff>=0.1.0\",\n496:     \"mypy>=1.5.0\",\n497:     \"pre-commit>=3.3.0\",\n498:     \"kubernetes>=28.0.0\",\n499: ]\n500: ```\n501: \n502: ### Python Version\n503: \n504: - `requires-python = \">=3.10\"`\n505: \n506: ### External Services\n507: \n508: - **Kubernetes Cluster**: Access via kubeconfig or in-cluster config\n509: - **Container Registry**: For image push operations (optional for local testing)\n510: - **Docker Daemon**: Required for local image building\n511: \n512: ## Documentation\n513: \n514: ### User Documentation\n515: \n516: 1. **Installation Guide**:\n517:    - Prerequisites (kubectl, Docker, Python 3.10+)\n518:    - Package installation: `pip install agentcube-cli[k8s]`\n519:    - Kubernetes cluster setup\n520: \n521: 2. **Getting Started**:\n522:    - Creating an agent workspace\n523:    - Packing an agent: `kubectl-agentcube pack`\n524:    - Building an agent: `kubectl-agentcube build`\n525:    - Publishing to Kubernetes: `kubectl-agentcube publish --provider k8s`\n526: \n527: 3. **Provider Documentation**:\n528:    - **Standard K8s Provider**: Using Deployment/Service resources\n529:    - **AgentCube Provider**: Using AgentRuntime CRDs\n530:    - Provider comparison and selection guide\n531: \n532: 4. **Command Reference**:\n533:    - `kubectl-agentcube publish` --provider k8s --namespace default --replicas 3\n534:    - `kubectl-agentcube publish` --provider agentcube --node-port 30080\n535: \n536: ### Developer Documentation\n537: \n538: 1. **Architecture Overview**:\n539:    - Provider abstraction layer\n540:    - Kubernetes API interaction patterns\n541:    - Error handling strategy\n542: \n543: 2. **API Reference**:\n544:    - `KubernetesProvider` class documentation\n545:    - `AgentCubeProvider` class documentation\n546:    - `PublishRuntime` integration\n547: \n548: 3. **Contributing Guide**:\n549:    - Running tests: `pytest tests/`\n550:    - Code style: `ruff check agentcube/`\n551:    - Type checking: `mypy agentcube/`\n552: \n553: ### Code Documentation\n554: \n555: - All public methods must have docstrings (Google style)\n556: - Complex logic must have inline comments\n557: - Type hints for all function signatures\n558: - Example usage in docstrings for key classes\n559: \n560: ## Security Considerations\n561: \n562: ### Kubernetes Authentication\n563: \n564: 1. **Kubeconfig Security**:\n565:    - Support multiple authentication methods (token, cert, exec)\n566:    - Never log or print kubeconfig contents\n567:    - Validate kubeconfig file permissions\n568: \n569: 2. **In-Cluster Configuration**:\n570:    - Use service account tokens when running in-cluster\n571:    - Validate service account permissions\n572:    - Implement RBAC requirements documentation\n573: \n574: ### Credential Management\n575: \n576: 1. **Registry Credentials**:\n577:    - Store securely in agent_metadata.yaml (file permissions)\n578:    - Support environment variables for sensitive values\n579:    - Never log credentials to stdout/stderr\n580: \n581: 2. **Session Tokens**:\n582:    - Store session_id in metadata (optional, may be sensitive)\n583:    - Clear session_id on context manager exit\n584:    - Support token rotation for long-running sessions\n585: \n586: ### RBAC Requirements\n587: \n588: **For Standard K8s Provider**:\n589: ```yaml\n590: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n591: kind: ClusterRole\n592: metadata:\n593:   name: agentcube-cli\n594: rules:\n595: - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n596:   resources: [\"namespaces\", \"services\", \"pods\"]\n597:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n598: - apiGroups: [\"apps\"]\n599:   resources: [\"deployments\"]\n600:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n601: ```\n602: \n603: **For AgentCube Provider**:\n604: ```yaml\n605: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n606: kind: ClusterRole\n607: metadata:\n608:   name: agentcube-cli-cr\n609: rules:\n610: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n611:   resources: [\"agentruntimes\", \"agentruntimes/status\"]\n612:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n613: ```\n614: \n615: ### Network Security\n616: \n617: 1. **Registry Access**:\n618:    - Support HTTPS-only registry connections\n619:    - Validate SSL certificates\n620:    - Support proxy configuration for secure environments\n621: \n622: 2. **Kubernetes API Access**:\n623:    - Prefer HTTPS for cluster communication\n624:    - Support custom CA bundles\n625:    - Validate API server certificates\n626: \n627: ### Data Protection\n628: \n629: 1. **Metadata File**:\n630:    - Set restrictive file permissions (0600)\n631:    - Exclude from version control (.gitignore)\n632:    - Support encryption for sensitive fields (future enhancement)\n633: \n634: 2. **Logging**:\n635:    - Redact sensitive information from logs\n636:    - Avoid logging full metadata contents\n637:    - Use structured logging with sensitive field redaction\n638: \n639: ## Future Enhancements\n640: \n641: ### Short-term Enhancements (0-3 months)\n642: \n643: 1. **Rolling Updates**:\n644:    - Implement zero-downtime deployments\n645:    - Support rolling update strategies\n646:    - Rollback capabilities\n647: \n648: 2. **Health Checks**:\n649:    - Enhanced readiness/liveness probe configuration\n650:    - Custom health check endpoints\n651:    - Health check status reporting\n652: \n653: 3. **Resource Management**:\n654:    - Resource limits and requests configuration\n655:    - HPA (Horizontal Pod Autoscaler) support\n656:    - VPA (Vertical Pod Autoscaler) integration\n657: \n658: ### Medium-term Enhancements (3-6 months)\n659: \n660: 1. **Multi-Cluster Support**:\n661:    - Deploy to multiple Kubernetes clusters\n662:    - Cluster selection via CLI flags\n663:    - Multi-cluster status aggregation\n664: \n665: 2. **Advanced Deployment Strategies**:\n666:    - Blue-Green deployments\n667:    - Canary deployments\n668:    - Traffic splitting support\n669: \n670: 3. **Observability Integration**:\n671:    - Prometheus metrics integration\n672:    - Distributed tracing support\n673:    - Custom resource metrics\n674: \n675: ### Long-term Enhancements (6+ months)\n676: \n677: 1. **GitOps Integration**:\n678:    - ArgoCD/Flux integration\n679:    - Git-based deployment manifests\n680:    - Automated synchronization\n681: \n682: 2. **Server-Side Apply**:\n683:    - Kubernetes server-side apply support\n684:    - Conflict resolution strategies\n685:    - Multi-ownership support\n686: \n687: 3. **Policy Enforcement**:\n688:    - OPA Gatekeeper integration\n689:    - Admission webhook support\n690:    - Policy validation hooks\n691: \n692: 4. **Cross-Cloud Support**:\n693:    - EKS, GKE, AKS specific optimizations\n694:    - Cloud provider resource management\n695:    - Cloud-native feature integration\n696: \n697: ## Implementation Checklist\n698: \n699: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider` class with all methods\n700: - [ ] Implement `AgentCubeProvider` class with all methods\n701: - [ ] Update `PublishRuntime` to support both providers\n702: - [ ] Update `StatusRuntime` to support both providers\n703: - [ ] Add provider selection logic in CLI\n704: - [ ] Implement namespace validation and creation\n705: - [ ] Add comprehensive error handling\n706: - [ ] Write unit tests for `KubernetesProvider`\n707: - [ ] Write unit tests for `AgentCubeProvider`\n708: - [ ] Write integration tests for publish flow\n709: - [ ] Add type hints to all public methods\n710: - [ ] Add docstrings to all public methods\n711: - [ ] Update user documentation\n712: - [ ] Create RBAC manifests\n713: - [ ] Add security validations\n714: - [ ] Implement logging and monitoring hooks\n\n(End of file - total 714 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider Design\n\n## AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider\n\n**Module**: `cmd/cli`\n**Language**: Python\n**Size**: M\n**Purpose**: Implement Kubernetes provider for agent deployment, enabling both standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service resources and AgentCube Custom Resources (AgentRuntime) for agent lifecycle management.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Overview\n\nThe Kubernetes provider enables the AgentCube CLI to deploy and manage agents on Kubernetes clusters using two deployment strategies:\n\n1. **Standard K8s Provider**: Creates native Kubernetes `Deployment` and `NodePort Service` resources\n2. **AgentCube Provider**: Creates `AgentRuntime` Custom Resources (CRD) managed by the AgentCube operator\n\nBoth providers share common interfaces through the `KubernetesProvider` and `AgentCubeProvider` service classes, which are integrated into the CLI via `PublishRuntime` and `StatusRuntime` classes.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-026/design.md","time":{"start":1775875592508,"end":1775875592527}}}}
